{
  "page": "Maynard Plumm",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Plumm\" title=\"House Plumm\"><img alt=\"House Plumm.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/50px-House_Plumm.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/75px-House_Plumm.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/100px-House_Plumm.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Ser</span><br />Maynard Plumm</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Plumm\" title=\"House Plumm\"><img alt=\"House Plumm.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/50px-House_Plumm.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/75px-House_Plumm.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/cf/House_Plumm.svg/100px-House_Plumm.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Maynard_Plumm_by_grandkhan.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Maynard Plumm by grandkhan.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/35/Maynard_Plumm_by_grandkhan.png/350px-Maynard_Plumm_by_grandkhan.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"423\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/35/Maynard_Plumm_by_grandkhan.png/525px-Maynard_Plumm_by_grandkhan.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/35/Maynard_Plumm_by_grandkhan.png/700px-Maynard_Plumm_by_grandkhan.png 2x\" /></a><div>Maynard Plumm, by Grandkhan ©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">Ser</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Plumm\" title=\"House Plumm\">House Plumm</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">Westerlands</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rawoiafmaynard_plumm.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rawoiafmaynard_plumm.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a></i> (appears)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Maynard Plumm</b> was a <a href=\"/index.php/Hedge_knight\" title=\"Hedge knight\">hedge knight</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/House_Plumm\" title=\"House Plumm\">House Plumm</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">Aerys I Targaryen</a>. He claimed to be distantly related to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_Plumm\" title=\"Viserys Plumm\">Viserys Plumm</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes_by_Maynard\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes by Maynard</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes_about_Maynard\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes about Maynard</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Theories\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Theories</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maynard_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Maynard_Plumm\" title=\"Category:Images of Maynard Plumm\">Images of Maynard Plumm</a></div>\n<p>Maynard was a tall, thin man with stooped shoulders. His blond hair was long and straight. Maynard wore dun-colored roughspun and stained brown leather, and a frayed cloak which was poorly dyed purple. The cloak was fastened with a large <a href=\"/index.php/Moonstone\" title=\"Moonstone\">moonstone</a> brooch which resembled a pale white eye in certain lighting.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Maynard was knowledgeable about current events in the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>, and he knew how to treat wounds.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maynard_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kyle_the_Cat_and_Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/57/Kyle_the_Cat_and_Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg/350px-Kyle_the_Cat_and_Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"167\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/57/Kyle_the_Cat_and_Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg/525px-Kyle_the_Cat_and_Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg 1.5x, /images/5/57/Kyle_the_Cat_and_Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Kyle_the_Cat_and_Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Kyle_the_Cat\" title=\"Kyle the Cat\">Kyle the Cat</a> and Maynard Plumm greet <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> at the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_tourney_at_Whitewalls\" title=\"Wedding tourney at Whitewalls\">wedding feast</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Whitewalls\" title=\"Whitewalls\">Whitewalls</a>. Illustrated by Mike S. Miller for the <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a></i> <a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight_(comics)\" title=\"The Hedge Knight (comics)\">graphic novel</a>.</div></div></div>\n<p>Ser Maynard was among the <a href=\"/index.php/Hedge_knight\" title=\"Hedge knight\">hedge knights</a> encamped by the <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye\" title=\"Gods Eye\">Gods Eye</a> near <a href=\"/index.php/Whitewalls\" title=\"Whitewalls\">Whitewalls</a>. He defended the actions of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden Rivers</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> known as Bloodraven, to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Kyle_the_Cat\" title=\"Kyle the Cat\">Kyle the Cat</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Maynard attended the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wedding\">wedding</a> of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Ambrose_Butterwell\" title=\"Ambrose Butterwell\">Ambrose Butterwell</a> and his <a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Frey_(wife_of_Ambrose_Butterwell)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lady Frey (wife of Ambrose Butterwell)\">new wife</a>, but he did not take part in the <a href=\"/index.php/Whitewalls_tourney\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whitewalls tourney\">tourney</a>. After Duncan the Tall lost to Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Uthor_Underleaf\" title=\"Uthor Underleaf\">Uthor Underleaf</a> in the lists, Dunk refused Maynard's advice to leave. When Dunk was cornered by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Cockshaw\" title=\"Alyn Cockshaw\">Alyn Cockshaw</a>, Maynard watched until Alyn had fallen into the well, then proceeded to help the injured Duncan and inform him his <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">missing squire</a> was safe in the castle's <a href=\"/index.php/Sept\" title=\"Sept\">sept</a>. Maynard claimed that Bloodraven knew of the conspiracy to crown <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_II_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon II Blackfyre\">Daemon II Blackfyre</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"Second Blackfyre Rebellion\">Second Blackfyre Rebellion</a> was indeed squashed by Lord Brynden's army the next morning. Duncan, Kyle, and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Glendon_Ball\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Glendon Ball\">Glendon Ball</a> looked for Maynard, but he had disappeared during the night. Duncan praised Maynard's assistance when he spoke with Bloodraven.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_by_Maynard\">Quotes by Maynard</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maynard_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes by Maynard\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/36/Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg/300px-Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"691\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/3/36/Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Maynard_Plumm_by_Mike_S_Miller.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Maynard Plumm reveals that <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden Rivers</a> knows about the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"Second Blackfyre Rebellion\">Second Blackfyre Rebellion</a>. Illustrated by Mike S. Miller for the <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a></i> <a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight_(comics)\" title=\"The Hedge Knight (comics)\">graphic novel</a>.</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Duncan</b>: We'd all be <a href=\"/index.php/Great_Bastards\" title=\"Great Bastards\">bastard sons</a> of old King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon</a> if half these tales were true.<br />\n<b>Maynard</b>: And who's to say we're not?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> and Maynard</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>A <a href=\"/index.php/Marriage\" title=\"Marriage\">marriage</a> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Melee\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Melee\">melee</a>, as any married man could tell you.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Maynard, to <a href=\"/index.php/Kyle_the_Cat\" title=\"Kyle the Cat\">Kyle the Cat</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>An honorable death is well and good, but if the life at stake is not your own, what then?<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;Maynard, to <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Duncan</b>: Who are you?<br />\n<b>Maynard</b>: A friend. One who has been watching you, and wondering at your presence in this <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Blackfyre_Rebellion\" title=\"Second Blackfyre Rebellion\">nest of adders</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a> and Maynard</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes_about_Maynard\">Quotes about Maynard</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maynard_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes about Maynard\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Stay well away from that one. He could be a <a href=\"/index.php/Robber_knight\" title=\"Robber knight\">robber knight</a>, for all we know.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>This close, there was something queer about the cast of Ser Maynard's features. The longer Dunk looked, the less he seemed to see.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan the Tall</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Maynard_Plumm&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font-size:90%;line-height:100%;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Ossifer_Plumm\" title=\"Ossifer Plumm\">Ossifer</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a 